{"id":"potsherd","term":"Potsherd","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A “shred”, i.e., anything severed, as a fragment of earthenware (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Job 2:8\">Job 2:8</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Proverbs 26:23\">Prov. 26:23</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 45:9\">Isa. 45:9</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Job 2:8","Proverbs 26:23","Isaiah 45:9"]}